Class FileInputOutput

  • java.lang.Object
    • FileInputOutput
  • public class FileInputOutput
extends java.lang.Object
    File input/output for both saved games in GameFile objects, as well as the Endgame Database, a mapping of boards hashcodes to evaluated GameValue objects.

      • addGameValueToDatabase

        public void addGameValueToDatabase​(int key,
                                   GameValue value)
        Adds the a key and value pair to the endgame database. Doesn't handle duplicates, so this must only be called after checking that the key doesn't already exist in the database, using the query method.
        Parameters:
        key - Key to add to the database, boards hashcode value
        value - Value to add to the database, GameValue for the board
